explanation: This solution uses a sliding window approach with a frequency map to efficiently track the frequency of characters within the current window. It iterates over the string, expanding the window to the right and updating the frequency map. If a window contains a single character that occurs at least thrice, it updates the maximum length. The solution has a high efficiency due to its use of a frequency map and a sliding window approach, but it has a quadratic time complexity due to the nested loops.

